# Optional environment overrides for local deploys. The CDK CLI normally sets
# CDK_DEFAULT_ACCOUNT / CDK_DEFAULT_REGION for you from your active AWS profile,
# so you rarely need this file — it documents the knobs app.py reads. Nothing
# auto-loads it (there's no dotenv dependency); `export` these or use direnv.
# Never commit real values: .env is git-ignored.

# Target AWS account and region for `cdk deploy`. Leave unset for environment-
# agnostic `cdk synth` (the default in CI).
# CDK_DEFAULT_ACCOUNT=123456789012
# CDK_DEFAULT_REGION=us-east-1

# Which local AWS credentials profile to use, if not "default".
# AWS_PROFILE=my-profile
